100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 22, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing pressing issues of disarmament and international peace amid rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the Scopes Monkey Trial continued to capture national attention as debates over evolution and education laws intensified. Meanwhile, in the Soviet Union, Joseph Stalin solidified his grip on power, signaling a shift toward more authoritarian governance.
